Package es.upm.pproject.miniproject.miniproject

Interface InterfaceEnrollmentManager

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    EnrollmentManager
    public interface InterfaceEnrollmentManager
    The EnrollmentManager interface facilitates the management of course enrollments and student registrations. It provides a set of methods to perform essential operations within the system, including registering courses and students, enrolling students in courses, canceling enrollments, restarting courses, and retrieving information about registered students and courses.

    EnrollmentManager acts as a centralized interface for administrators to interact with the system, ensuring efficient and reliable handling of course-related tasks. It encapsulates the core functionalities required for course and student management, promoting modularity and maintainability of the codebase.

    Key functionalities provided by EnrollmentManager include:

    • Registering Courses: Allows administrators to register new courses by providing unique identifiers, titles, and coordinator names.
    • Registering Students: Enables the registration of new students with unique identifiers, names, and email addresses. It ensures that the email addresses are valid and unique.
    • Enrolling Students: Facilitates the enrollment of students in courses, ensuring that each student can be enrolled in a course only once and that courses do not exceed their maximum capacity.
    • Canceling Enrollments: Provides functionality to cancel a student's enrollment in a course, removing them from the course roster.
    • Restarting Courses: Allows administrators to restart courses, canceling all active enrollments in the process and resetting the course to its initial state.
    • Retrieving Student and Course Information: Offers methods to retrieve lists of all registered students and courses, enabling administrators to view and manage the system's data.

    EnrollmentManager ensures handling error conditions effectively. It utilizes exception handling mechanisms to communicate errors and failures, enabling robust error recovery and fault tolerance.

    • Method Detail

      • registerCourse

        void registerCourse​(int code,
                    java.lang.String name,
                    java.lang.String coordinator)
             throws CourseAlreadyExistsException,
                    CourseBlankInputException
        It registers a new course.
        Parameters:
        code - Specifies the unique course identifier. Must be a positive integer.
        name - Specifies the title of the course.
        coordinator - Specifies the name of the person coordinating the course.
        Throws:
        CourseAlreadyExistsException - when the course's code is already registered in the database.
        CourseBlankInputException - when any of the input parameters are blank or null or the code is not a positive integer.
      • An example of use is provided below:
      • registerCourse(1, "Computer Science 101", "Coordinator 1") will successfully register the course.
      • registerCourse(1, "", "Coordinator 1") will throw a CourseBlankInputException().
      • registerCourse(1, "Computer Science 101", null) will throw a CourseBlankInputException().
      • registerCourse(-1, "Computer Science 101", "Coordinator 1") will throw a CourseBlankInputException().
      • registerCourse(0, "Computer Science 101", "Coordinator 1") will throw a CourseBlankInputException().
      • registerCourse(1, null, "Coordinator 1") will throw a CourseBlankInputException().
      • registerCourse(1, " ", "Coordinator 1") will throw a CourseBlankInputException().
      • registerCourse(1, "Computer Science 101", " ") will throw a CourseBlankInputException().

      • registerStudent

        void registerStudent​(int id,
                     java.lang.String name,
                     java.lang.String email)
              throws StudentAlreadyExistsException,
                     StudentBlankInputException,
                     EmailFormatException
        It registers a new student.
        Parameters:
        id - Specifies the unique student identifier. Must be a positive integer.
        name - Specifies the student's name.
        email - Specifies the student's e-mail address. It must contain a '@' and cannot end with a '.'.
        Throws:
        StudentAlreadyExistsException - when the student's id or e-mail is already registered in the database.
        StudentBlankInputException - when any of the input parameters are blank or null or the id is not a positive integer.
        EmailFormatException - when the email ends with a '.' or does not contain '@'.
      • An example of use is provided below:
      • registerStudent(1, "Student 1", "student1@example.com") will successfully register the course.
      • registerStudent(-1, "Student 1", "student1@example.com") will throw a StudentBlankInputException().
      • registerStudent(0, "Student 1", "student1@example.com") will throw a StudentBlankInputException().
      • registerStudent(1, "", "student1@example.com") will throw a StudentBlankInputException().
      • registerStudent(1, "Student 1", "") will throw a StudentBlankInputException().
      • registerStudent(1, " ", "student1@example.com") will throw a StudentBlankInputException().
      • registerStudent(1, "Student 1", " ") will throw a StudentBlankInputException().
      • registerStudent(1, null, "student1@example.com") will throw a StudentBlankInputException().
      • registerStudent(1, "Student 1", null) will throw a StudentBlankInputException().
      • registerStudent(1, "Student 1", "student1.example.com") will throw an EmailFormatException.
      • registerStudent(1, "Student 1", "student1@example.") will throw an EmailFormatException.

        StudentAlreadyEnrolledException - when the student is already enrolled in the course.
